name: Defeat 01 - Benito mussolini
description:
April 28, 1945, 16 hours and 10 minutes, Benito Mussolini and his lover Clara Petacci are captured and executed by a commando of communist partisans in Giulino di Mezzegra, Como region, a small town in northern Italy near the border with Switzerland .During his escape he is captured and shot 'like a mad dog'. Their bodies are exposed and desecrated in a Milan gas station.

DEFEAT It is a collection based on people whose death historically had an impact on power, quite remarkable in history, either by homicide, convictions or natural deaths, these people marked the beginning, or the end of a corrupt era within universal history.
